# Session 17 Handover — Fumage

## What was done this session

### New article — The Invisible Third (`/guide/layering`)
Fragrance layering guide, registered as article 22 in the guide index. Merged from two source articles: the new article's six verified brand-specific combinations (Molecule 01 / Iso E Super as amplifier, Tobacco Vanille + Bergamote 22, Encre Noire + Amber Pour Homme, Santal 33 + Baccarat Rouge 540, Oud Wood + Sauvage, Black Afgano + Bleu de Chanel EDP) with the prior HTML article's unique content: scent pyramid visual, when-to-layer occasions, numbered application steps, hair mist technique, soliflore-as-tool method, drydown layering, seasonal ratio rotation, seven pitfalls, Kurkdjian closing quote, and "start with two bottles" conclusion. The user's editorial voice (practical, accessible, occasion-aware) was preserved in the body sections it originated. Commit `fe0b118`.

### New interactive tool — Layering Tool (`/layer`)
Interactive fragrance layering tool added as a dedicated route and linked from the main nav (between Dupes and Guide on desktop and mobile). Architecture:

- **`/app/layer/page.tsx`** — server shell with metadata
- **`/app/layer/LayeringTool.tsx`** — client component. Three labeled search slots (Base / Top / Accent) with Meilisearch autocomplete via the existing `/api/search` endpoint. Selecting a fragrance triggers a fetch to the new `/api/layer/[slug]` route for full note data. When two or more slots are filled, the blend result panel renders.
- **`/api/layer/[slug]/route.ts`** — new Prisma route returning structured note data (TOP / MIDDLE / BASE / ACCORD), performance scores, family, subfamily, seasons, and occasions for a given fragrance slug.
- **Blend result panel** contains: (1) combined notes pyramid with pills color-coded by source fragrance and shared notes highlighted as structural bridges; (2) projected performance bars (longevity / projection / sillage averaged across selections); (3) family profile with contextual guidance per family count; (4) rule-based blend assessment built from note overlap count, averaged performance, season and occasion intersections. No external API calls — fully computed from Prisma catalog data.
- AI-generated description deferred — designed to be added later as a `/api/layer/predict` route calling the Anthropic SDK.

Commit `8cc4ba2`.

